
[1]thred

   THRED, n.

   1. A very small twist of flax, wool, cotton, silk or other fibrous
   substance, drawn out to considerable length.

   2. The filament of a flower.

   3. The filament of any fibrous substance, as of bark.

   4. A fine filament or line of gold or silver.

   5. Air-threads,the fine white filaments which are seen floating in the
   air in summer, the production of spiders.

   6. Something continued in a long course or tenor; as the thread of a
   discourse.

   7. The prominent spiral part of a screw.
